## ‚ö†Ô∏è Situations to Avoid

- Representing any entity **not owned or managed by SAS**  
- Accepting payment or favors for filing lawsuits on someone else‚Äôs behalf  
- Speaking in court on behalf of another company (even if you helped form it) unless SAS owns it  
- Representing Top Notch on matters over $15,000 without a lawyer  
- Letting others (e.g. subcontractors) speak on behalf of Top Notch in court

